What mean of OOP ?
 - Object-oriented programming is about creating "objects", which can hold data and functions that work on that data.

What we seen ....
 1. Classes and Object
 2. Encapsilation 
 3. Abstraction
 4. Polymorphism
 5. Inheritance
 6. Access Modifier
 7. Operator Overloading
more ....

